import { useState } from 'react-dom' import Workouts from '../components/Workouts' import NewWorkout from '../components/NewWorkout' import Templates from '../components/Templates' import NewTemplate from '../components/NewTemplate' function Dashboard(props) { const buttonController = (e, type) => { e.preventDefault() switch (type){ default: return case "Workouts": return case "NewWorkout": return case Templates: return case newTemplate: return } } buttonController() return(

Welcome to Your Dashboard {props.name}

  • buttonController(e, "workouts")} href="#">Your Workouts
  • buttonController(e, "newWorkout")} href="#">New Workout
  • buttonController(e, "templates")} href="#">Your Templates
  • buttonController(e, "newTemplate")} href="#">New Template
) } export default Dashboard;
